6
00:01:42.170 --> 00:01:47.840
Ebisu Town

7
00:01:50.250 --> 00:01:53.220
All right, we're counting on you, good sir.

8
00:01:54.040 --> 00:01:55.880
Leave it to me.

9
00:01:57.500 --> 00:02:00.520
I will take it upon myself...

10
00:02:00.520 --> 00:02:06.440
to lay Yasuie's body to rest in Kuri.

11
00:02:19.210 --> 00:02:21.870
Please provide him with the utmost of care.

12
00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:24.290
Naturally...

13
00:02:24.780 --> 00:02:30.800
We, too, are greatly indebted to Lord Yasuie...

14
00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:36.840
We're all set! Let's get
a move on, Nami and Kanjuro!

15
00:02:37.290 --> 00:02:38.390
Okay!

16
00:02:38.390 --> 00:02:41.310
Ah, I will be right there! Let us make haste!

17
00:02:45.240 --> 00:02:48.530
Have a safe journey!

18
00:02:52.860 --> 00:02:57.320
Wano Country
Kibi
Ringo
Flower
 Capital
Kuri
Udon
Hakumai
Oni

19
00:02:53.530 --> 00:02:57.320
At a dock on the way from the Flower Capital to Kuri...

20
00:02:58.410 --> 00:03:04.290
To capture the vile fugitives who
made an attempt on Lord Orochi's life,

21
00:03:04.730 --> 00:03:08.670
we've set up checkpoints
all around the Flower Capital!

22
00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:15.970
All of you, show your faces!

23
00:03:16.650 --> 00:03:17.590
What should we do?

24
00:03:18.520 --> 00:03:21.720
It looks like our escape won't be so easy.

25
00:03:22.360 --> 00:03:26.060
We can't get to Kuri
if we don't get on that boat.

26
00:03:26.060 --> 00:03:29.710
We've gotta figure out a way past it.

27
00:03:45.850 --> 00:03:47.290
What?!

28
00:03:51.590 --> 00:03:56.800
A curse on you!

29
00:03:59.080 --> 00:04:02.140
Th-They're being haunted by a ghost!

30
00:04:03.050 --> 00:04:05.620
Y-You may pass!

31
00:04:09.370 --> 00:04:12.140
We got through somehow...!

32
00:04:12.750 --> 00:04:14.150
How's Otoko?

33
00:04:14.150 --> 00:04:18.280
She's all tuckered out from crying
and is fast asleep in my arms.

34
00:04:21.790 --> 00:04:26.160
I honestly don't know what to say to her...

35
00:04:26.330 --> 00:04:28.920
Daddy!

36
00:04:36.170 --> 00:04:37.760
Daddy!

37
00:04:51.730 --> 00:04:53.770
Bonekichi, give her to me.

38
00:04:53.770 --> 00:04:56.440
You don't provide enough warmth.

39
00:04:57.750 --> 00:04:58.740
How cruel!

40
00:05:07.820 --> 00:05:09.660
That's not true, is it...?

41
00:05:14.290 --> 00:05:14.340
Southwest Kuri

42
00:05:14.290 --> 00:05:19.260
Southwest Kuri

43
00:05:23.820 --> 00:05:26.970
Th-Those are...!

44
00:05:26.970 --> 00:05:28.020
Ships?

45
00:05:28.020 --> 00:05:28.980
Ships...

46
00:05:28.980 --> 00:05:30.940
Ships!

47
00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:38.230
I'm speechless, Ashura!

48
00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:40.610
They'll need a bit of work...

49
00:05:41.390 --> 00:05:46.580
but we salvaged them from all of
Wano's harbors that Kaido laid to waste.

50
00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:51.870
These are enough to ferry thousands
of warriors to Onigashima!

51
00:05:52.400 --> 00:05:57.290
You are quite dependable!
My opinion of you has improved!

52
00:05:57.290 --> 00:06:01.970
Yes, mine too. You were never
known to be so sensible.

53
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:09.100
It's not as if I was asleep for twenty years!

54
00:06:09.700 --> 00:06:14.310
I will ask Master Franosuke
to service these later!

55
00:06:15.750 --> 00:06:20.190
The journey thus far
has been long and arduous,

56
00:06:23.730 --> 00:06:28.690
but now the day of the raid is within sight!

57
00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.510
Onigashima

58
00:06:49.900 --> 00:06:53.770
I'm sure I knocked the ship
off of the waterfall...

59
00:06:53.770 --> 00:06:57.650
King, you bastard!
Always doing things half-assed!

60
00:06:57.650 --> 00:07:01.260
Queen, Bro... Why did you bring her here?

61
00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:06.110
Shut up! We lost comms in Udon!
What was I supposed to do?!

62
00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:09.660
King!

63
00:07:10.790 --> 00:07:14.530
I'll forget what you did to me,

64
00:07:14.530 --> 00:07:16.670
if you join me.

65
00:07:22.170 --> 00:07:27.720
All kinds of people live in
my country... except for three.

66
00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:32.640
One of them seems to have dwindled
and faded into the mists of time...

67
00:07:33.150 --> 00:07:35.140
yet here you stand in the flesh.

68
00:07:35.140 --> 00:07:36.390
I refuse!

69
00:07:42.570 --> 00:07:44.400
That's too bad.

70
00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:47.710
Well, unlock these handcuffs already.

71
00:07:47.710 --> 00:07:50.870
What the hell do you mean, "Well"?!
Forget it, you old bag!

72
00:07:51.320 --> 00:07:52.820
Have you heard?

73
00:07:53.950 --> 00:07:59.420
Big Mom and Viceroy Kaido were once
part of the same pirate crew.

74
00:07:59.420 --> 00:08:04.340
What's going on here? Set her free.

75
00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:08.680
– Viceroy Kaido!
– Viceroy Kaido!

76
00:08:09.050 --> 00:08:12.390
So you finally showed your face, Linlin.

77
00:08:16.300 --> 00:08:18.020
Kaido.

78
00:08:29.440 --> 00:08:32.950
Hey, you! You were told to set me free.

79
00:08:32.950 --> 00:08:34.900
– What?!
– What?!

80
00:08:34.900 --> 00:08:37.910
No way! It had to have been a joke...

81
00:08:38.340 --> 00:08:39.460
Set her free!

82
00:08:40.010 --> 00:08:41.290
Kaido...!

83
00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:52.930
How many decades has it been...?

84
00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:54.710
Napoleon!

85
00:08:59.180 --> 00:09:00.940
Yes, Mama!

86
00:09:00.940 --> 00:09:04.060
It's so good to have you
back to your normal self!

87
00:09:04.060 --> 00:09:06.650
I'm so shy around strangers,
I couldn't do anything!

88
00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:11.410
I told you I'd kill you
if you showed your face here.

89
00:09:11.850 --> 00:09:14.950
What idiot travels this far
to her own execution?

90
00:09:56.030 --> 00:09:58.080
The 
Next
 Day

91
00:09:58.080 --> 00:09:59.950
Oihagi
 Bridge

Ringo

92
00:10:12.810 --> 00:10:13.880
Two-Sword Style...

93
00:10:15.050 --> 00:10:17.720
Seven-Twenty-Pound Phoenix!

94
00:10:28.480 --> 00:10:30.530
I have more weapons than you!

95
00:10:38.070 --> 00:10:40.330
What's your deal, anyway?!

96
00:10:41.700 --> 00:10:43.330
Are you friend... or foe?!

97
00:10:46.310 --> 00:10:47.920
Who the hell are you?!

98
00:11:01.020 --> 00:11:06.440
Why are you ripping off weapons
from people who cross the bridge?!

99
00:11:06.910 --> 00:11:09.230
Just give me back my sword.

100
00:11:09.690 --> 00:11:13.940
Don't throw away your life
over a single blade.

101
00:11:28.940 --> 00:11:32.460
I cannot allow its return! I shall
give you any sword but that one!

102
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:45.310
The blade you carried was Shusui,
a national treasure stolen from Wano!

103
00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:49.690
What? Shusui?!

104
00:11:49.690 --> 00:11:54.070
Our misfortune began
the moment it was taken!

105
00:11:54.960 --> 00:11:57.530
The God of the Blade grew wrathful,

106
00:11:57.980 --> 00:12:03.700
bringing defeat after defeat to each region,
until the entire country fell to the invaders!

107
00:12:08.050 --> 00:12:09.290
What's this "god" drivel?!

108
00:12:10.500 --> 00:12:12.710
Blasphemer!

109
00:12:31.200 --> 00:12:33.770
Cease your fighting!

110
00:12:50.250 --> 00:12:56.280
What could compel a samurai and a monk
to fight out in the remote countryside?

111
00:12:56.280 --> 00:13:00.180
What's most humorous is that
neither of you intend to kill the other!

112
00:13:00.990 --> 00:13:01.800
A fishman?

113
00:13:27.240 --> 00:13:29.740
Kawa... matsu...

114
00:13:30.210 --> 00:13:32.670
Kawamatsu?! Is that you?!

115
00:13:34.590 --> 00:13:36.210
How do you know my name?!

116
00:13:40.670 --> 00:13:43.340
Oni-
gashima

117
00:13:43.980 --> 00:13:46.080
When are they gonna stop fighting?!

118
00:13:46.080 --> 00:13:48.430
Should we evacuate to the mainland?!

119
00:13:48.430 --> 00:13:50.480
Listen up, men!

120
00:13:51.550 --> 00:13:54.980
What kind of idiot would run away
while the boss is fighting?!

121
00:13:54.980 --> 00:13:56.860
You buncha babies!

122
00:13:57.240 --> 00:13:59.000
Queen, when'd you get here?

123
00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:00.690
You ran away, too?!

124
00:14:02.850 --> 00:14:05.830
Th-That's not what happened...

125
00:14:09.420 --> 00:14:11.790
Anyway, any word from Udon?

126
00:14:11.790 --> 00:14:15.170
About that, the smail still isn't connecting.

127
00:14:17.090 --> 00:14:20.760
Alright! I'll go check it out!

128
00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:23.950
His Awesomeness is trying to escape! No fair!

129
00:14:23.950 --> 00:14:25.890
No, I said, "I'll go check it out!"

130
00:14:30.490 --> 00:14:32.060
Give me that!

131
00:14:31.330 --> 00:14:32.060
Ah, yes, sir!

132
00:14:34.910 --> 00:14:36.730
Yo, this is Queen!

133
00:14:36.730 --> 00:14:39.650
– All right! Queen!
– All right! Queen!

134
00:14:39.650 --> 00:14:43.820
This is Warden Babanuki in Udon.

135
00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:47.490
Right. It looks like the smails are back online.

136
00:14:47.490 --> 00:14:48.990
Yes, as of just a moment ago.

137
00:14:49.560 --> 00:14:52.080
I took a lot of men back with me.

138
00:14:52.080 --> 00:14:55.040
We can head your way if you're short-handed.

139
00:14:55.040 --> 00:14:57.780
What a cool way to look
for an excuse to leave!

140
00:14:57.780 --> 00:15:00.420
That won't be necessary for now.

141
00:14:59.670 --> 00:15:00.420
Tch!

142
00:15:00.420 --> 00:15:02.090
– Denied!
– Denied!

143
00:15:02.510 --> 00:15:05.090
Straw Hat Luffy, Captain Kid,

144
00:15:05.090 --> 00:15:08.850
and all the troublemakers
are locked in their cells.

145
00:15:09.250 --> 00:15:10.410
I see...

146
00:15:10.410 --> 00:15:12.760
So, I called to tell you all is well.

147
00:15:12.760 --> 00:15:13.980
Tell me all is wrong!

148
00:15:13.980 --> 00:15:15.690
Your Awesomeness!

149
00:15:15.690 --> 00:15:22.570
Prisoner
 Mining 
Camp

Udon

150
00:15:18.210 --> 00:15:20.840
Over and out.

151
00:15:22.570 --> 00:15:25.860
How was that, Master?!

152
00:15:26.250 --> 00:15:28.740
Good job! Thank you!

153
00:15:29.350 --> 00:15:30.370
You're a good boy!

154
00:15:30.370 --> 00:15:32.200
I sure am!

155
00:15:33.830 --> 00:15:35.670
What sort of sorcery is this?!

156
00:15:35.670 --> 00:15:38.760
A millet dumpling tamed the enemy!

157
00:15:40.380 --> 00:15:43.880
They seem to work on animals
and those with animal powers.

158
00:15:45.490 --> 00:15:48.090
It all went so swimmingly.

159
00:15:49.370 --> 00:15:52.070
And we have you to thank, Caribou!

160
00:15:52.070 --> 00:15:54.180
Oh, yes!

161
00:15:54.180 --> 00:15:57.060
It's all thanks to me!

162
00:15:58.060 --> 00:16:03.900
Now, the enemies outside think that thousands of
us prisoners are just sitting quietly in our cells!

163
00:16:04.350 --> 00:16:10.130
I wonder how surprised the enemy
will be on the day of the battle!

164
00:16:13.410 --> 00:16:15.450
You owe me!

165
00:16:15.450 --> 00:16:17.100
Understood!

166
00:16:17.100 --> 00:16:21.080
Terrific! We can finally
contact Kin'emon's group.

167
00:16:23.250 --> 00:16:24.960
Dr. Chopperemon!

168
00:16:25.450 --> 00:16:30.550
We swear we will repay you for this,
even if it costs us our lives!

169
00:16:30.550 --> 00:16:34.520
It's fine. It was a relatively easy virus to treat.

170
00:16:34.520 --> 00:16:37.640
Besides, a samurai's debt would be
too much of a burden for me.

171
00:16:38.100 --> 00:16:39.810
Th-Thank goodness!

172
00:16:40.850 --> 00:16:42.480
Even Luffytaro's all better...

173
00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:45.150
Let's go, you guys!

174
00:16:45.150 --> 00:16:46.860
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

175
00:16:46.860 --> 00:16:49.030
– Luffytaro!
– You're the man!

176
00:16:49.030 --> 00:16:50.990
– Let's do it!
– That's what I'm talking about!

177
00:16:50.990 --> 00:16:53.740
He seems healthy and popular again.

178
00:16:54.990 --> 00:16:58.830
Thanks to Lord Momonosuke bringing
him here, he has earned their trust!

179
00:17:00.610 --> 00:17:02.000
There's no mistaking it.

180
00:17:02.380 --> 00:17:04.460
He has not changed a bit...

181
00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:06.710
It has been so long...

182
00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:09.010
Boss Hyogoro!

183
00:17:15.720 --> 00:17:17.430
Oh, it's them!

